article.headline: Wichita State 68, Hampton 65
article.story: CHARLOTTE AMALIE, U.S. Virgin Islands (AP) -- Jamar Howard had 17 points and eight rebounds to lead Wichita State to a 68-65 victory over Hampton at the Paradise Jam tournament Sunday night. The lead changed six times in the final minutes of the first half. The Pirates (1-1) seized the lead at 18-17 with 6:45 left and gave it up twice, the last time for good. The Pirates closed within a point, 66-65, with 13 seconds left. Howard then made the first of two free throws to give Wichita State a 67-65 lead. Hampton's Rodney Hughes grabbed the rebound, but fell and attempted to pass to Jeff Granger. Howard tied up Hughes, and the possession arrow was in favor of the Shockers (2-0). Fridge Holman was fouled with seven seconds remaining. He made one of two free throws, extending the Shockers' lead to three points. Hampton's Jared Woodley missed a 3-point attempt as time run out. Aaron Hogg scored 14 points for Wichita State. Holman, Rob Kampman and Paul Miller each added 11 points. Woodley scored 24 points to lead the Pirates. Devin Green had a double-double with 18 points and 10 rebounds.
